page.content: As our area is largely residential it is therefore covered by houses, flats, some tower blocks, maisonnettes and bungalows. A small section is covered by park land, two fairly large parks, Maryon Park and Maryon Wilson Park. Our school is called Woodhill, the same name as the street. Years ago they were both known as Wood Street. In those days the area was very wooded. There is still a large number of trees in the Woodhill area and of course both the parks contain many trees and a great variety of trees also. Where our school stands the area was thickly wooded but this was a long time ago as our school celebrated its centenary in 1983. It is now the only large building in the area, apart from a tall block of flats. It is also a listed building under the Greenwich Borough Council.
